Apical sternite (
Fig. 35
) transverse, divided in two lobes, emarginated apically and with a cluster of black, strong bristles; yellow, with brown apical-lateral parts; apical tergite (
Fig. 34
) approximately semicircle to rectangular shaped, transverse, 1.6 times longer than wide, evenly roundly emarginated on anterior side, covered with sparse, black, long bristles and a row of short setae on anterior margin; yellow with brown apical-lateral parts. Median lobe (
Figs. 37
) simple, almost completely straight with thin, stretched and very ventrally curved apex; massive rounded and sinuate lamella; internal sac distinct, showing a number of small denticles. Tegmen wide, enlarged on sides, 1.2 times longer than wide, moderately emarginated apically, with very short thin appendages (
Fig. 36
).
